709751f.title: Manhattan: 7th Avenue - 31st Street (West)
709751f.text:
Seventh Avenue, west side, south from West 33rd to 31st
Street's, showing the excavation for the Pennsylvania
Railroad Station. This will occupy this entire two scuare
blocks; Eighth Avenue being on the right. The additional
excavation in the right center is for the power house that
will be located on the opposite side of 31st Street. The
R. C. Church and School of St. John the Baptist appear at
the left. The school is on 31st Street and the church on
30th Street.
About 1907
Ewing Galloway
NO RIPRODUCTIOIS

709754f-a.title: Manhattan: 7th Avenue - 31st Street (West)
709754f-a.text:
Seventh Ave., west side, north from West 31st, to and including West
34th Streets, showing the Pennsylvania Railroad Station, as it extends
to West 33rd Street. In the right background is seen the Nelson Tower,
between West 34th and West 35th Streets.
1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Writers Project.

709742f.text:
Seventh Avenue, west side, from W. 31st to 33rd Street, showing
the automobile runway at Pennsylvania Station. The station proper
is on the left; W. 31st Street on the right, and 7th Avenue in the
background.
1939
Alexander Alland
NO REPRODUCTIOIS
